{"ts":"2026-06-27T17:23:15.974Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Compliance Data**\n\nI've recently focused on displaying compliance-related information within the interface. I've integrated a card that showcases compliance rule data. This includes counts for total rules, health statuses, and validation details, specifically for standards like ISO-27001, SOC2, and HIPAA. I intend to make these metrics dynamically update based on the current system state, allowing for precise tracking of these standards.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T17:23:17.697Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Integrating the Logstream**\n\nI'm now integrating a secure shell telemetry logstream into the UI, including connection status indicators and dynamic display of logs. I've designed the visual layout for the logstream, including styling for headers and the log display, alongside a connection seal indicator and a telemetry heartbeat cycle message. I'm focusing on ensuring it handles dynamic updates and displays logs with a timestamp. The goal is a clean, informative terminal for telemetry and debug.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
