{"ts":"2026-06-27T17:23:28.330Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the Interface**\n\nI am currently focused on designing the code for a precise replacement of a specific section to incorporate improved information boxes, updated cards with hover effects, and live terminal logs. I am starting with the HTML structure, beginning with a div element.\n\n\n**Refining the UI Elements**\n\nI'm currently working on the visual components, specifically focusing on a card for cluster hardware health. I'm leveraging Tailwind classes for rounded corners, borders, background, and spacing. The structure includes a header with an icon and a subheading. I'm using an array to map and render information about different nodes, including labels, specifications, ping times, and load percentages, which should be dynamic. I need to make sure the load percentages are representative and informative, and will ensure this.\n\n\n**Implementing the Node Card**\n\nI've finalized the structure and design for a node card. I used Tailwind for styling, including text colors, fonts, spacing, and borders. The card is composed of a header, node information, and an isolated memory seal section. I've designed the node information section to display labels, specifications, ping times, and load percentages. The isolated memory seal section showcases the cryptographic protection of memory enclaves. I believe this card is now a good foundation.\n\n\n**Constructing New Cards**\n\nI'm now implementing new cards for active enclaves and running AI operations. They utilize WorkspaceCard components with specific Tailwind styling for a consistent look. I've included icons and dynamic data placeholders, intending to display critical information about project enclaves and AI operations, such as total counts and active status indicators. I will work towards integrating these into the broader UI flow.\n\n\n**Adding Compliance Data**\n\nI've recently focused on displaying compliance-related information within the interface. I've integrated a card that showcases compliance rule data. This includes counts for total rules, health statuses, and validation details, specifically for standards like ISO-27001, SOC2, and HIPAA. I intend to make these metrics dynamically update based on the current system state, allowing for precise tracking of these standards.\n\n\n**Integrating the Logstream**\n\nI'm now integrating a secure shell telemetry logstream into the UI, including connection status indicators and dynamic display of logs. I've designed the visual layout for the logstream, including styling for headers and the log display, alongside a connection seal indicator and a telemetry heartbeat cycle message. I'm focusing on ensuring it handles dynamic updates and displays logs with a timestamp. The goal is a clean, informative terminal for telemetry and debug.\n\n\n"}}
